Papillary Thyroid Carcinoma related diagnostic biomarker target development and targeted drug selection

Author: Qianhui Yang        Research use only

  • 1.Intro(Introduction)
  • 2.Query(Genetic expression and clinical data from TCGA)
  • 3.DifGene(Screening differentially expressed genes of each subtype)
  • 4.seriescluster(Analyzing the differentially expressed genes of each subtype distinguished from other subtypes)
  • 5.Boxplot(DEG box plot)
  • 6.GOPathway(DEG KEGG and GO analysis)
  • 7.Mutation(analysis of the correlation between specific genes of each subtype and typical mutant gene)
  • 8.expressinmutdrivergene(analysis od the correlation between specific genes of each subtype and typical mutant gene)
  • 9.Stargene(specific gene and immune correlation analysis of each subtype)
  • 10.ImmuneScore(analysis of the correlation between specific genes and immune index and immune cell abundance of each subtype)
  • 11.GenePanel(screening survival-related gene panels in the classical subtype)
  • 12.GenePanel(screening the gene panel associated with lymph node involvement in each subtype)
  • 13.GeneSelect(the status of each subtype screening gene)
  • 14.Cmap(analysis of the correlation between genes associated with lymph node involvement in various subtype)
  • 15.Tool(software and database)

Differential gene screening

Method:

The comparison group for this analysis:ClassicalVSControl,FollicularVSControl,TallCellVSControl

Algorithm:DESeq2--Counts(Needs Rep)

Screening creteria: log2FC > 1 , FDR < 0.05

Conclusion:

Among the three types of papillary thyroid carcinoma， Tall Cell subtype has most specific difference genes （4025 up-regulated，2630 down-regulated），Follicular subtype has the least specific difference genes （2251 down-regulated，1920 up regulated）,Classical subtype has 4948 DEGs .

Result:

Table:Overall significant difference genes statistics (download from here)

Compare Algorithm Log2FC_Cutoff FDR_Cutoff AllGeneNum UpGeneNum DownGeneNum
ClassicalVSControl DESeq2 1.0 0.05 27831 2582 2366
FollicularVSControl DESeq2 1.0 0.05 26511 1920 2251
TallCellVSControl DESeq2 1.0 0.05 25505 2630 4025

Table note:Compare:compare group names

   Algorithm:Algorithms used to perform significant differential gene screening。

   Log2FC_Cutoff:Threshold of significant difference gene screening。

   FDR/P_Cutoff:P value difference significance level,indicating the probability whether the gene is a difference gene;FDR is the multiple hypothesis test error misjudgment rate

   AllGeneNum:All differentially exoressed genes

   UpGeneNum:the number of genes that are significantly upregulated

   DownGeneNum:the number of genes that are significant downregulated
